Description: CVE-2026-25988 - Fix MSL stack index not refreshed leading to leaked images
 The MSLPushImage function did not return the updated stack index, so
 callers could not track the current position. This caused images to be
 stored in the wrong slot and never freed on error paths, leading to
 memory leaks and potential denial of service through resource exhaustion.
 The fix changes MSLPushImage to return the new stack index (ssize_t)
 and updates the call site to capture the returned value.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/d2e99064d65f5955f39d92e4b208089409118683
Author: ImageMagick Developers <imagemagick-developers@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2025-02-25

