Description: CVE-2026-33899 - Fix heap buffer overflow via integer underflow in XML parser
 In NewXMLTree function, an integer underflow during UTF-16 to UTF-8
 character conversion leads to a single null byte being written out of
 bounds when length is zero, corrupting heap metadata. This patch adds
 an early return with proper error handling when length is zero, before
 the vulnerable utf8[length-1] access.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/149326dd993e8833e42e35d21bacaa0c98e11c34
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-04-15

--- a/magick/xml-tree.c
+++ b/magick/xml-tree.c
@@ -2003,6 +2003,13 @@
       return((XMLTreeInfo *) NULL);
     }
+  if (length == 0)
+    {
+      utf8=DestroyString(utf8);
+      (void) ThrowMagickException(exception,GetMagickModule(),OptionWarning,
+        "ParseError","root tag missing");
+      return((XMLTreeInfo *) NULL);
+    }
   terminal=utf8[length-1];
   utf8[length-1]='\0';
   p=utf8;
Description: CVE-2026-46523 - Disable blob support for MSL image format
 The MSL coder registration did not disable blob support, allowing
 potential security issues when processing MSL format images. This patch
 sets blob_support to MagickFalse for the MSL coder.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/5ad5fdcc45871bdeeca414a883acb880532accce
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-05-21

--- a/coders/msl.c
+++ b/coders/msl.c
@@ -7945,6 +7945,7 @@
   entry->encoder=(EncodeImageHandler *) WriteMSLImage;
 #endif
   entry->format_type=ImplicitFormatType;
+  entry->blob_support=MagickFalse;
   entry->description=ConstantString("Magick Scripting Language");
   entry->magick_module=ConstantString("MSL");
   (void) RegisterMagickInfo(entry);
Description: Fix CVE-2026-33536 stack-buffer-overflow in InterpretImageFilename
 An incorrect return value from FormatLocaleString on certain platforms can
 cause subsequent length-dependent logic in InterpretImageFilename
 (magick/image.c) to operate on a malformed buffer, leading to a 1-byte
 stack-buffer-overflow WRITE (CWE-121, GHSA-8793-7xv6-82cf).
 .
 The upstream fix (commit 3ed2120f7 in ImageMagick/ImageMagick6) targets a
 refactored implementation that uses a separate stack pattern[] buffer and
 advances a cursor by the formatted length. ImageMagick 6.9.11-60 (this
 target) predates that refactor and uses a fundamentally different in-place
 format-rewriting algorithm that writes directly into the caller-supplied
 filename buffer at filename+(p-format-offset).
 .
 This patch hand-ports the upstream invariant into the legacy code path:
 capture the FormatLocaleString return value, and bail out (return 0) if
 the call failed (count <= 0) or if writing count bytes at the computed
 offset would exceed MaxTextExtent. This preserves the security guarantee
 of the upstream fix while remaining minimal and ABI/API-compatible with
 the 6.9.11-60 series shipped in Debian 11.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/3ed2120f70ee9ff0c6cac2375e5821c52c381b4c
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-8793-7xv6-82cf
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-19

--- a/magick/image.c
+++ b/magick/image.c
@@ -1671,6 +1671,7 @@ MagickExport size_t InterpretImageFilename(const ImageInfo *image_info,
     *p;

   ssize_t
+    count,
     field_width,
     offset;

@@ -1697,8 +1698,11 @@ MagickExport size_t InterpretImageFilename(const ImageInfo *image_info,
         q++;
         c=(*q);
         *q='\0';
-        (void) FormatLocaleString(filename+(p-format-offset),(size_t)
+        count=FormatLocaleString(filename+(p-format-offset),(size_t)
           (MaxTextExtent-(p-format-offset)),p,value);
+        if ((count <= 0) ||
+            ((ssize_t) (p-format-offset+count) >= (ssize_t) MaxTextExtent))
+          return(0);
         offset+=(4-field_width);
         *q=c;
         (void) ConcatenateMagickString(filename,q,MaxTextExtent);
Description: CVE-2026-49218 - Added missing check for returning an image with zero columns or rows
 ImageMagick's DCM (DICOM) decoder in ReadDCMImage was missing a check
 for zero rows or columns. A crafted DICOM file with Rows=0 and/or
 Columns=0 produced a zero-dimension Image* that could cause denial of
 service in downstream operations. This patch adds a guard that returns
 a CorruptImageError ImproperImageHeader when the decoded image has
 zero rows or columns.
 .
 Tracked as GHSA-8pj9-6897-74xc.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/14faf35495e9191f54bc63df44383a76f5cf16d9
Author: Dirk Lemstra <dirk@lemstra.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-17
--- a/coders/dcm.c
+++ b/coders/dcm.c
@@ -4364,6 +4364,8 @@
   if (image == (Image *) NULL)
     return(image);
   (void) CloseBlob(image);
+  if ((image->rows == 0) || (image->columns == 0))
+    ThrowReaderException(CorruptImageError,"ImproperImageHeader")
   if (status == MagickFalse)
     return(DestroyImageList(image));
   return(GetFirstImageInList(image));
Description: CVE-2026-25983 - Fix heap-use-after-free in MSL parser
 ImageMagick has a heap-use-after-free vulnerability in coders/msl.c.
 A crafted MSL script triggers the operation element handler to replace
 and free an image while the parser continues reading from it, leading
 to a UAF in ReadBlobString during further parsing. This patch adds
 bounds checking (n < 1) before all image null checks in MSLStartElement
 and MSLEndElement to prevent mutations on the first image, and reorders
 variable initialization in repage/roll handlers to occur after the
 safety check.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/95db8ba0f445a798e823a86acdebe97de73de449
