Description: CVE-2026-33905 - Fix out-of-bounds read in SampleImage()
 An out-of-bounds read vulnerability exists in ImageMagick's -sample
 operation when a specific offset is configured through the sample:offset
 define. The SampleImage() function pre-allocates an x_offset buffer and
 fetches entire source rows, which can result in out-of-bounds memory
 access when offset values are manipulated. This patch replaces bulk
 offset pre-allocation with per-pixel on-demand calculation and restores
 the PseudoClass/CMYK guard condition.
