Description: CVE-2026-46521 - Fix OOB write in MIFF LZMA encoder
 The buffer-size calculation in WriteMIFFImage omitted LZMAMaxExtent
 from the MagickMax(...) computation, and the lzma_easy_encoder
 status check had an inverted assignment (status=MagickTrue on
 success). Both issues could lead to an out-of-bounds write when
 encoding MIFF images with LZMA compression.
 .
 Backported from upstream ImageMagick6 commit 61adf32.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/61adf32771284186f2fbaea220062226123ac394
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-jcqp-6r6f-3mfx
Author: ROOT.io Patch Platoon <security@root.io>
