Description: CVE-2026-56370 - validate object indices in ConnectedComponentsImage
 ConnectedComponentsImage() in magick/vision.c could write past the end of
 the per-object array when a user-supplied artifact (e.g.
 connected-components:keep-ids, :remove-ids, :keep-top) referenced an object
 id outside the [0, component_image->colors) range. The unchecked indices
 led to out-of-bounds writes into the object[] array.
 .
 This patch adds bounds checks around each indexed merge assignment so that
 only ids within the valid range update object[i].merge, preventing the
 out-of-bounds writes. See the upstream advisory:
 https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-pmpg-6pww-fg6q
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/60b4e60841b429d719c59144e2505c8b0135367d
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-27
--- a/magick/vision.c
+++ b/magick/vision.c
@@ -543,7 +543,9 @@
         }
       step=(ssize_t) (first > last ? -1 : 1);
       for ( ; first != (last+step); first+=step)
-        object[first].merge=MagickFalse;
+        if ((first >= 0) &&
+           (first < (ssize_t) component_image->colors))
