Description: Fix CVE-2026-47166 heap buffer over-read in distributed pixel cache
 An attacker who connects to a magick -distribute-cache service can send a
 read command with an oversized length field that exceeds the actual pixel
 buffer, causing dpc_send to read past the buffer boundary and leak heap
 memory. This patch adds ValidateDistributedPixelCache bounds checking on
 all server-side read and write operations, and hardens the session key
 protocol by switching from CRC32 (GetMagickCoreSignature) to SIPHash24
 with a proper challenge-response handshake, changing session_key type from
 size_t to uint64_t for platform independence.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/81589e7209b72bb84442380ff53109f61d41902d
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
