Description: Fix CVE-2026-33535 stack-buffer-overflow in XImageWindowCommand
 An out-of-bounds write of a zero byte exists in the X11 display interaction
 path (XImageWindowCommand in magick/display.c). The delta buffer (allocated
 on the stack) was indexed using strlen(delta) without bounds checking,
 leading to a stack-based buffer overflow when processing long sequences of
 numeric key symbols. This patch caches strlen(delta) and adds a bounds check
 against MagickPathExtent before writing the digit, and reorders the writes
 so the character is written before the null terminator.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/3bdfa6a73a6c0ba5f2d0986cd2a1892c37f796f3
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-19

